title: Østensjø
text:
Østensjø () is a <a href="List%20of%20boroughs%20of%20Oslo">borough</a> of the city of <a href="Oslo">Oslo</a>, <a href="Norway">Norway</a>.
The borough is in the southeastern part of Oslo. It is well known for its proximity to the forested area of <a href="%C3%98stmarka">Østmarka</a>, a popular resort and hiking area for the citizens of Oslo and <a href="L%C3%B8renskog">Lørenskog</a>. Østensjø consists of the suburbs of <a href="B%C3%B8ler">Bøler</a>, <a href="Oppsal">Oppsal</a> and <a href="Manglerud">Manglerud</a>, all located around Lake <a href="%C3%98stensj%C3%B8vannet">Østensjøvannet</a>. The Østensjøvannet area has been a protected wildlife reserve since 1992.
Østensjø has traditionally been a <a href="Norwegians">Norwegian</a> middle and working class borough, compared to the more <a href="Immigration%20to%20Norway">immigrant 
populated</a> areas in <a href="East%20End%20and%20West%20End%20of%20Oslo">Oslo East End</a>.
The club <a href="IL%20Manglerud%20Star">IL Manglerud Star</a> which is known for <a href="Manglerud%20Star%20Ishockey">ice hockey</a> and <a href="Manglerud%20Star%20Toppfotball">football</a> is located here.
